Here’s some of my recent work. Friendly reminder — I’m not taking new clients or projects right now and I don’t know when I will be booking new clients again. Don’t worry, I make sure to have space for ongoing projects and established regular clients! 

My schedule is pretty set until mid May and I’m going to be taking a big chunk of time off next summer so I don’t have a set date for when my books will reopen to new projects and clients. 

Any last minute openings will be posted on my IG stories and given to the first person to email, so turn on your notifications for that if you’re interested. 

Without getting too personal on here, I’ve had a lot of heavy unexpected life stuff happen over this fall/winter, and coming to work has been such a joyful reprieve from all of it! I’m wildly grateful for the intrepid and beautiful souls who are brave enough to sit in my chair and dive headfirst into the experience of getting tattooed. All my love to you! 

Take care of yourselves and each other. It’s a hard world out there. We can get through this together. ❤️‍🔥
More recent tattoos! These are a mix of flash and custom pieces. The last slide is healed a couple years, the rest are fresh. Thanks for looking.❤️‍🔥

Brought in a live model reference for this one! Thanks @milla_oliva_ for grabbing some sweet candid shots of me tattooing one of my all time faves @emilycolangelo at @lilithtattooseattle 🌱❤️‍🔥 also shoutout to @popspark, @kaiatattoos, and @lub.dub.tattoo for mentoring me and helping me continue to hone my color technique. 

I love doing color tattoos and I’m actively working to improve my saturation and get clean solid heals with a single pass. I’m thrilled to have lovely and trusting clients who support me as I continue to push my learning edge. 

Tattooing is incredibly difficult. I’ve been doing this professionally for just over three years (after surviving a traditional apprenticeship and spending a lifetime being a self taught artist) and the more I learn, the less I realize I know. 

Anyone who says they find tattooing to be easy probably can’t even pull a clean line and generally will be held back by their own hubris. 

Pay your dues, approach this sacred craft with respect, learn from people who have been doing it longer than you. Put in the work. New tattooers, you are not reinventing the wheel. Your work speaks for itself. Be humble.
Here’s a custom piece for Mo ❤️‍🔥 I loved the concept they had in mind and I’m so happy with how this delicate piece came together. Thanks again! It was lovely to meet you.

Healed plus some fresh additions for Krista. I love working this way — finishing pieces each time but leaving room to grow if we decide to add more. Thanks for the trust and great conversation. I still can’t believe you brought me the most gorgeous carnivorous Nepenthes Ventrata. This perfect plant is one of the coolest things I’ve ever been given. I named the pitchers Eros and Thanatos and they’re getting their first lil bug snacks today 🥰🥰🥰

For the record — I never expect tips or gifts! I know tattoos are so expensive and it’s a huge honor that folks save for a long time to come get my artwork, and I don’t take that lightly at all. Showing up to your appointment hydrated and well fed is enough! But also, the generosity and kindness of my clients never ceases to amaze me. You all are the absolute best and I’m so excited for the many incredible projects I have coming up. All my love to you! 

A blessed solstice, Io Saturnalia, Happy Hanukkah, Merry Christmas, whatever you celebrate this time of year I hope it’s warm, cozy, and abundant with love and connection.

UPDATE — All spots are spoken for. Thank you sooooo much for your enthusiasm and interest in my work! I can’t believe I filled an entire flash day in like 45 minutes 😭😭😭 y’all are the best. 

—————

So the rumors are true… I’m having a flash day on Christmas, this Sunday the 25th at @lilithtattooseattle ! 

Escape your family’s clutches after opening your gifts and spend your Christmas or Hanukkah money on a new tattoo! Piss off your parents twice in one day! (Just kidding, moms love me). 

This is *not* a walk-in event, you must email me and book an appointment to secure a time slot with a deposit. Happy to get friends or siblings in back to back too! 

Each of these designs will be offered at a generous flat rate of $200 (my usual minimum). Palm sized-ish or smaller, I’m open to adjustments. I’m leaning towards arms and legs only but could be convinced otherwise. Haha. 

I’m happy to do these pieces as just linework or with shading, with or without sparkles, with or without the pops of red, but no other mods please. I’m also happy to make the nails blue if you’d like them to be Hanukkah nails! 

These will be shaded in my usual style, this is just a digital mock-up so it isn’t exact. Y’all know what my work looks like! It’s gonna be cute and fun. 

I will be repeating all of these designs for one day only, so don’t worry about needing to claim a specific piece. You can have whatever you want! 🥰

To claim your spot, email me at prometheatattoos@gmail.com and put “12/25 flash” in the subject. 

In the body of the email, let me know which one you’d like (antlers, mistletoe, pinecone, champagne, holly, ghost, or capricorn !)

It’s okay if you change your mind on the day too. 

Thanks so much for another wonderful year in the books and I can’t wait to spend Christmas with you! 

Xoxo 🧑🏻‍🎄🌲❄️✨❤️‍🔥

Healed Ægishjálmur — this was an incredibly badass first tattoo and I’m *so* happy with the heal. Now for Keith’s second tattoo we’re doing his entire back! Thanks again for your trust and friendship. 

I would love to do more bind runes, traditional magical staves, and custom sigils. We can always add these pieces onto an existing appointment. Let me know your intentions/desired outcome and I can create a sigil for the exact magical working you have in mind. This is a great way to craft an intention and set things into motion in the new year. Be mindful about what you choose to call into being, this stuff works really well 🤣 ask me how I know. 

Getting to tattoo the Helm of Awe felt really special after spending extended time in Iceland this year (one of my ancestral homelands). Powerful stuff. 

Thanks for looking!

I had so much fun making this custom skull planter + crystal piece for Leona. This was based on a favorite little planter they have at home, it was so fun putting my spin on their lovely reference photo. They are also a @lilithtattooseattle all star client with tattoos from most of us, what a feat! I wish we had a punch card, but for now you just get sweet tats and bragging rights. Thanks again Leona, I can’t wait to see ya again in a couple months ❤️‍🔥

Here are some chest piece additions for one of my all time faves, thee Aquarian cryptid enthusiast @jerynpasha ❤️‍🔥 The center parts are over a year healed. We also did some cute thorny hearts around their nips last Valentine’s Day so it’s a whole mood. 

I love working this way — finishing a piece to completion and then adding more after you live in it for awhile. This was so fun! Thanks again Jeryn, you’re the best 🗡🗡🗡

Here’s a few little bangers from 🐐♑️ season ❤️‍🔥 fresh and healed. Cool text in the first slide is not by me, but I get a lot of satisfaction in placing my work to compliment your existing pieces. It feels like collaborating with talented people I’ve never met and I love that. 

Thanks for looking and for getting tattooed by me! I’m still not booking new clients and won’t be for awhile but I promise I’ll make an announcement when I’m ready to do that! 

Thanks for the interest in my work 🥰
2023 so far 🥰❤️‍🔥 thanks for supporting my art and helping me live my lifelong dream of a stable, healthy, fulfilling existence. I’m glad I stuck around for this chapter of my life.
This was done in two sessions, linework is healed and color is fresh. Thanks Becca! So excited to take on more color projects like this and keep growing my skills 🥰

Kiki has been one of my clients since the beginning of my time at Lilith. She’s incredible. All the work on her left arm is mine. We’ve built such a rad friendship over the last few years. 

Her sweet husband reached out to me last year about booking a surprise appointment for her birthday to help finish her sleeve, what a thoughtful gift! I love fun surprises. 

Anyway, we did this gigantic chrysanthemum in One. Damn. Session. I think this is the largest single piece I’ve ever done in one shot.

Kiki is a warrior and I am in awe of her resilience and commitment (inside and outside the tattoo shop). Getting tattooed is not for the faint of heart, and sitting for a whole day is a spiritual rite of passage for sure. 

Love you Kiki, thanks for your trust in me and for your support and friendship. Also, thanks for making me laugh hysterically all day. So grateful for you!

Update — all spots booked ⚡️

Happy Aquarius season! 

I’m stoked to announce that I’m booking my next official flash day. This flash day is ✨Appointment Only✨— on Sunday, February 12th. 

In the true Aquarian spirit of innovation and progress, I’ve created pieces that will continue to push my art style and technique forward into the future. 

Additionally, because Aquarius is always eccentric and individualistic (while still being the ultimate humanitarian at its core) I am allowing some customization on these pieces! You can combine them, we can piece them around or in between existing tattoos, we can create a composition with or without black stars, with or without lightning (we love a little Uranian zap⚡️) and as always size and placement is up to you! 

Because these pieces are a bit more involved, they won’t be offered at a flat rate. I will give you an estimate for your specific piece once we begin our correspondence (range will be between $250 and $400 depending on final size, placement, and design elements chosen).

If you’re interested in booking one of these for 2/12, email me with “Aquarius flash” in the subject line, and let me know the details of which piece(s) you want, any customizations, and what placement you have in mind. I will require a $100 deposit to book your spot, and that will come off the final cost of your tattoo. 

Also, if you’re an Aquarius, or have ♒️ in your big three, you get booking priority, so let me know in the email. The designs available are — rippling pool, cherub, vase, impossible triangle, orchid, sword, star portal, and cosmic skull head. Lightning or stars can be done on their own or added to any piece to make it fit your body and tattoo collection perfectly. 

Also, the shading on the sheet is just a mock-up, it isn’t an exact representation of what your finished tattoo will look like. I will be doing my usual dotwork and pepper shading in addition to the black fill.

As always, thanks for looking and for your interest in my work!

Here’s a little collection of some of my January bangers 🥰 thanks for coming in! I have lots of exciting projects on the books this spring, both big and small. I love it all! 

Booking is still closed for now, I will announce when I’m booking again, promise. I’m taking some extended time off this summer as I have been planning my life out wayyyy too far in advance, so I’m going to give myself a break from that for a bit. Books are currently full until mid May and then I’m falling off the grid for a second. 

As always, thanks for looking and supporting my work! It’s so appreciated.

Artio + her menagerie in the forest for Lindsey. This is mostly healed with some fresh on the back part. Thanks for your trust over the years! I’ve done some big pieces on Lindsey’s leg too. 

It’s exciting to get to do more color work. It’s such a patient process and often requires multiple sessions but it’s so worth it. 

Swipe to the last side for a little drawn on lagniappe 😉 if you come see me a few times a year (and do really good accents like Lindsey) maybe I’ll tattoo your fingers. Just maybe.
Here’s a custom memorial piece I made for Samantha to honor the life of her sister. Thank you for the trust ❤️‍🔥

@_notjordan_ requested a scorpion in a more traditional style and I had so much fun making it! Bring on the 9RLs and mags! 

I love bold lines and heavy black just as much as the delicate pretty stuff. I do it all 🤓 Don’t be afraid to ask for what you want!

I approach all of my tattoos with a spirit of collaboration. Making your dreams come true and helping your ideas come to life keeps me growing as an artist as well! 

I don’t ever want to stick to one type of tattooing, I plan to become proficient in as many styles and techniques as I can in this lifetime (big ♊️ probs 🤣). Thanks for the trust Jordan. ❤️‍🔥

when you’re a tat goddess and you have a day off 💅🏼🌸🌷💐🌺🌹🌼✨ 

big thanks to Sydney @the.spiritspa for making me feel refreshed and renewed inside and out 🍄🌱❤️‍🔥

Check out this set I made for Olivia! Mermaid is from this week, made to complement Athena on the other thigh that I made 2 years ago (🤯🤯🤯). 

I included some close ups of her perfect heal. It’s such an honor to have repeat clients who come see me year after year. 

When I did the Athena piece, I was just one year old (!!!) in the tattoo world! It was done at my learning edge and I’m still so proud of it. 

It’s rewarding to be learning and improving all the time, and still look back on my older work and really love it while appreciating how far I’ve come. Seeing work settle and age so beautifully after years of being lived in is such an incredible feeling.

If you’re ever going to a new artist, make sure they post their healed photos somewhere, especially pieces that are over a year old! You can also contact them and ask for some images of healed work. Having zero healed photos anywhere in their online portfolios or social media is a bit of a 🚩🚩🚩 in my opinion.

Thanks again for your trust! I wake up every day excited to do this work and collaborate with you all on your dream tattoos. 

I will never be a flash only artist. I thrive on personal and artistic evolution, and I love the challenge of making your ideas come to life. ❤️‍🔥

✨⚡️🏺♒️Aquarius ♒️🏺⚡️✨
flash day at @lilithtattooseattle was a huge hit! Thanks everyone for coming out. 

As a triple ⚔️air⚔️ sign (Gemini 🌞, libra 🌙 & ⬆️) I love my Aquarius bbs. We adore our little aliens of the zodiac! 

Many thanks to my professional cherub for hire @sacredbraid who kept my station perfect and fed me a BLT and cookies and provided lots of comic relief. 

I am really enjoying these astro themed flash days and plan to keep them going for every sign! 

If there’s anything specific you wanna see on the flash sheet during *your* upcoming season, drop your sun sign and your idea in the comments!

We all know Valentine’s Day is a loaded and commercial holiday, but I’m here for the kitsch and camp of it all. Cringe is dead. Seize joy and delight however you can, be free. 

I am a summation of every person I’ve ever loved — the ones who broke my heart, the ones who I broke theirs. Every person I’ve ever been intimately close to is still with me. The memories of connection are all interwoven with the present, it’s almost as if time doesn’t exist and I’m loving all of them simultaneously. 

Sometimes I have to remind myself that opening my heart is worth the risk. Maybe I’ll try again someday. 

Mostly, this Valentine’s Day I’m thinking about how I’m finally truly at home in myself, in this form, in this body, in this life, and how for so many years I wondered if I’d ever feel like this. 

The work is worth it. Loving yourself in a world that is constantly telling you that you shouldn’t exist or that you should disappear is a feat of strength. I have risen to the occasion. I have come back home to myself over and over again. Healing is not linear, and it’s worth all of the hard work. I am a force. 

I wouldn’t be where I am without the fierce platonic love I feel for my dear friends and creative community. 

Whatever type of love you’re leaning into today — eros, philia, storge, or agape — I hope it’s sweet and nurturing. I hope it provides a soft reprieve from the hard edges and sharp corners of existence.

Healed Medusa by @judeletronik ❤️‍🔥
Photo taken at @the.spiritspa 🌷

I finally got to do a proper tattoo for my dear friend José! This is a piece I drew for him years ago, at the tail end of my apprenticeship (swipe for the original drawing). It was a birthday gift for him in March of 2019. 

When I drew it, I had only done a couple of very simple tattoos on skin, and I told him he had to wait for me to get good enough at tattooing to do it justice. Well, the time finally came. 

Doing this piece was powerful for me, it reminded me of all the art I used to make for myself before I steered my creativity to do so much custom work for others. Making this made me feel so inspired and like I’m coming back home to myself creatively. 

I could gush about José and how we’ve worked and lived together on boats in many different oceans, traveled the world together, had some of the wildest adventures on multiple continents… but the caption would be too long. Love you José! Now you get to keep me close to your heart forever ❤️‍🔥

Also, I got to use a 45 mag for the first time doing this piece, and my god it was so satisfying! Swipe to see the gravedigger / claw o’ the beast suckin up ink out of a rinse cup (the only sterile vessel I had that was large enough to use as an ink cap). Side of ranch ramekin vibes. 

Don’t be surprised if you see lots of wannados from me in the future with large deliberate areas of fill so I can use these beastly needle groupings more often 😅

Thanks for lookin!

I love creating tattoos that weave stories together and create narratives over the arc of your life — pieces that are always at a point of completion, but that can also grow and evolve with you. 

I did the left side of this (the eight of cups piece) for client-turned-friend @cadydidnt almost two years ago, and a few months back she came to me with the interest of adding on with some fool imagery.

We drew on most of this, and I’m loving the folksy illustrative style and how our story is unfolding. That’s the thing about tarot imagery, the archetypes are malleable and kind of ebb and flow into each other. It was a fun challenge to illustrate that abstract, illusory, cosmic consciousness type of feeling that arises when working closely with tarot. 

Thanks for trusting my creative liberties on this one (the ace of cups to signify your deep well of emotional intelligence) and to have the fool’s hounds be your doggies 🥰 can’t wait to work with you again!

I’ve had so much fun working on Kadedera’s leg over the last few years!We started at the top of her foot and ankle two and a half years ago (!!!) with florals and a hummingbird, then we added some flowering cannabis, then butterflies and swirling notes from her favorite song, then most recently some strawberries and a big butterfly. 

I can’t wait to see this new piece of the puzzle all healed and settled with the rest. Swipe to the end to see the freehand and stencil I did for this last session.

Thank you for being a wonderful client and friend @k.love_24 ❤️‍🔥 I live for our Gemini mind melds! ⚡️♊️✨

I have so many fun tattoos I need to post 🙈 I had such a great time making this piece inspired by Rafaello Monti’s “Veiled Lady” sculpture… in shades of purple! 

We laid down some soft black shading and texture and then blasted right over it with shades of violet, fig, and lilac. Swipe for the process and a photo of the sculpture. 

I’m so happy with this one, I’d love to do more textured statuesque pieces (especially with interesting color stories!). 

You’re the best Cailyn, so lovely to meet you and thank you spending the first part of your birthday with me! 🥰
High contrast Great Blue Heron for Steph 🥰 I would love to do more in this style! Also I’m obsessed with using 45 mags to pack color, that’s all.

Here’s a flash piece I did for Nicole. Lines are healed 6 months or so and color/shading is fresh. 

I am in the process of gutting my entire flash book and making all new designs for when my books open on 6/1. Established clients and people with ongoing projects can email me on 5/20 and you will get first priority for booking.

My new flash consists of pieces of all sizes, including small gap fillers you can add on to your session, and larger multi-session pieces with specific placements in mind. I’m cookin’ up some really cool stuff 😎 Can’t wait! 

I’m wrapping up as many of my current projects as I can before my hiatus from work mid May - mid June. It feels good to let my calendar run out and I will be back with all the excitement to do your summer projects! So start scheming 😉 thanks for all the support and interest in my work.

UPDATE: all spots spoken for, deposits pending. If anyone drops out I’ll post their spot on my stories!

It’s time for Pisces flash day! I’ll be booking these designs today for this coming Sunday, 3/5! This way, folks who can’t plan their schedule too far ahead will have a chance to sneak on my books. 

All of these pieces will be between $250 and $350 depending on final size and placement. I can give you an estimate once I hear your ideas. Email me today to book an appointment for this Sunday. Each spot requires a $100 deposit to book. 

The shading on this sheet is just a mock-up, it’s not exact. These pieces will be shaded in my usual style. I am happy to do with or without bubble and star adornments, but other than that, no modifications please. 

If you are a Pisces sun or have it in your big three, let me know ya crybabies! I’ll give you priority. My Mars is in Pisces and while I kind of hate it, I’m pretty sure that’s why I’m not a complete airhead/insensitive asshole (triple air sign problems amirite!?). 

To book a spot for this Sunday, email Prometheatattoos@gmail.com — put “Pisces flash day” in the subject line, and in the body of the email let me know which one you want, and if you have any specific ideas about placement or size. Happy crying season! Hope you get to drink wine, smoke joints, dissociate, and sob in a bathtub at least once.

I’m getting worse at staying on top of posting here and better and better at tattooing 😎 I make art, *not* content. 

Here are some fun ones from last month that I never got around to sharing! 

My books open 5/20 for return clients, 6/1 for new clients! This will be for July & August appointments.
My interpretation of epic monster goddess Echidna from Greek mythology on Charlia 🥰🥰🥰 More monsters, more claws, more glorious belly tats please! Thanks again, it was so lovely working with you. ❤️‍🔥
Here’s a little collection of some recent flash and custom pieces for your viewing pleasure. Thanks for looking! ❤️‍🔥

In light of all the discourse surrounding Darren Aronofsky’s film “The Whale,” I thought I’d share some art depicting fatness and the experience of living in a fat body made by an actual fat person, me. Here’s a lovely healed photo a client sent me recently. For the record, I haven’t seen “The Whale”, and I won’t be watching it. 

I’ve been fat my entire life. I firmly believe that my body is the least interesting thing about me, but for some reason it’s the thing about me that people seem to fixate on. 

When my work started gaining traction on social media a couple years ago, it seemed like my talent, my ability to connect with people, and my unstoppable drive to create paled in comparison to the size of my body and my willingness to live unapologetically in it. 

I was constantly touted for my “bravery” and “confidence” simply for existing joyfully and not actively trying to change myself. This has always bothered me. 

Like, how is it seen as such an impossible feat to be joyous, successful, beautiful, adored, and even sexually desired in a fat body? 

Well, I’m here to tell you it’s not impossible, and fat people are not a monolith. We’re not all wretched unloveable creatures who hide in the shadows stuffing our faces. Maybe some of us are, but I know plenty of thin people who live in misery like that. 

Just because you might harbor an intense fear of being fat, and this fear keeps you from living a full life, doesn’t mean that people who are actually fat live in a constant state of misery and discomfort. That’s your story, not mine.

The most discomfort I experience in my body is when I have to deal with the constant projections of thin people and other insecure folks trying to use me as a confidence prop or validation for thoughts like “at least I’m not *that* fat”. 

When I tell people about my experience growing up in a high demand religion (yes, a cult), the hellish childhood I escaped from, the intense trauma I’ve survived, how I’ve been on my own for so long, and all of the extraordinary adventures I’ve had, they seem so shocked. 

Continued in comments cause I’m long winded and verbose ⬇️⬇️⬇️
Chaos portal for my best friend of 20+ years. Love you @ann_poindexter ❤️‍🔥

I typically only post finished tattoos but I was too excited about the start we got on this one! 

Here’s Salome and John the Baptist with some funeral flowers for @whosthatghoull 🖤 she sat super tough for the line work, I know the next session where we do shading and detail will be a breeze. Thanks again Colleen! You’re a treasure! 

This piece was a one-off wannado that I posted awhile back. I have more large concepts in the works that will be available when my books open on 6/1 🤓 can’t wait!

Let’s gooooooooooooo 🔥🔥🔥

In the chaotic, intrepid, fire-starting spirit of Aries season, I booked a week long solo spring trip to Berlin eight days in advance of leaving. 😅

I’ve been working myself to the bone for the last six months without much reprieve and have felt the need for a break even before my big planned hiatus this summer. Being my own boss is hard, I’m my own strictest task master and I often don’t recognize my burnout until it’s too late. 

It’s especially challenging when I love my work on an obsessive level, it’s hard to tear myself away from it even when it’s necessary (ask my sister or any of my patient and loving close friends who have been trying to make plans to hang out with me for months 😂).

I had some openings come up in my schedule at the end of March, so I moved the rest of my people (thank you!!!) and decidedly flew the coop to Germany. 

Berlin is one of my most favorite cities in the entire world. Simultaneously old and new, historic and cutting edge, relaxing and exciting, structured and chaotic. I love it. I always feel like I’m overflowing with artistic inspiration after visiting such a dynamic, beautiful, and culturally rich place. 

An important part of being a full time artist and existing successfully in a creative vocation is making time to take breaks from producing. It’s crucial to venture out into the world and collect inspiration, be thrilled and challenged, and give yourself the gift of meeting new people and having new experiences.

My cup is now full again and I’m excited to pour it into all the beautiful tattoos I have on the books over the next month! Can’t wait to hang out with my lovely clients and make you some unforgettable masterpieces! As always, thank you for your support and interest in my work. You getting tattooed by me means I get to live my dreams, and I don’t take that lightly at all. 

I can’t wait to abundantly share and pour out the inspiration I’ve collected in the form of some lovely tattoos on incredible humans! 😊🥰😘

Here are some lavish peonies I made for long time client Mackenzie ❤️‍🔥 She wanted more of an etching linework style for these which was exciting to execute! I will always love doing floral linework, especially in the springtime. It makes me feel romantic and hopeful 🥰

Also, it was so satisfying to create the composition using both stencils and freehand to make it fit perfectly around her existing tattoos. Swipe to the end of the carousel for a video.

All other pieces pictured are by me and healed various ages (1-3 years) except for those cool black florals on the front and back of her arm by @crapric0rn 🖤 what a collection! 

Thanks again Mackenzie, I’m excited to see what you scheme up for your next piece.

Candace came all the way from Utah to get this custom wraparound tattoo from me. When she emailed me with this concept (a kraken attacking a ship in a violent sea) I jumped at the chance to execute it. I’m always touched that people want *me* to do their tattoo, especially when they have to cross state lines to do it! 

Did I mention that it’s only her second tattoo ever, and her other one is a tiny piece behind her ear!?! So brave! 

I’m really proud of this piece, I think it showcases how much I’ve been working to hone and refine my technique. I used different line weights to signify the perspective, I made sure there was a good amount of negative space in the composition, and I put a lot of thought and intention into where everything landed on her arm. I can’t believe we knocked this out in five and a half hours. 

Thanks again for your kindness and trust Candace, I can’t wait to have you back for more in the future!

(Backstory — I left a sassy comment flexing on a viral video of a full back piece being completed in a scant six hours by a group of tattooers while the client was under anesthesia. It’s Gemini season, I can’t help myself… sorry not sorry. I earned the bragging rights for sitting for this. Swipe for earlier in-progress photos and close-ups of some sections. 

This masterpiece took about 20 sessions and was done in 60 hours or so over a two year period by the inimitable @nrrdcakke at @jacksonstreettattoocompany ❤️‍🔥 

She’s been tattooing for 14 years now and is a seasoned pro, not to mention an absolute delight to work with.

Each session was anywhere from two hours to six hours. Our longest was the last one, where I sat for around seven hours. There is an entire black and gray finished underpainting that we completed first, then we did the layers of color on top. 

Good tattoos take time to heal and complete. The process should not be rushed. Masterworks like this require many layers to achieve this level of complexity and saturation, and grays heal lighter than they look after the initial sessions when they’re still fresh. 

Being fast is not something to brag about, but that said, Alivia is one of the most clean and efficient tattooers I’ve ever met. The only touch up we needed was a spot I scratched in my sleep 🤣

And yes, I’m fat, I have a BIG ASS back. It would be the size of a goddamn area rug if you skinned me and laid it out in your living room. I wouldn’t have it any other way. This piece would not be nearly as majestic and striking if I was any smaller. No shade to my smaller babes out there, but us big babes have the real estate to really go to town. 

Thanks for looking. Stay mad haters! 🫶

To me, it often feels like pride is centered heavily around thin yt people in able bodies, and that bums me out. I didn’t escape Mormonism at a young age and come out a couple decades ago just to be forced to the fringes by a homogenized culture *again*. 

Let’s remember to include everyone when celebrating. Fighting racism and facism starts with being inclusive of *ALL* queer folks, not just the ones who happen to meet the heteronormative Eurocentric (and ultimately facist) standards for existing in a body. 

Don’t forget, striving to meet an “ideal” body type is deeply rooted in xenophobia, purity culture, neo-puritanical Christian ethics, and some pretty dangerous and harmful political ideologies that I don’t need to name. Body diversity is beautiful.

This magical time of year marks the celebration of Litha, also known as the summer solstice, the longest day of the year. 

I am typically an autumnal/winter witch, but I’ve really leaned into the bright magic of the spring and summer this year. I mean, I am a Gemini after all, I’m allowed to contain multitudes.

Then today, my first full day back at home in almost 5 weeks, I took myself to @the.spiritspa for some physical and spiritual rejuvenation. It feels so good to sink back into myself after such a grand adventure. I’m beyond grateful to be alive in this wild time, in this abundant and healthy body, in this community, in this world, in this exact iteration. 

I feel so ready to get back to work tomorrow! I can’t wait to share all the killer projects I have on the books this summer.

I feel like pop astrology has condensed most of the astrological signs into extremely flat and simplified one note ideas of their most extreme traits… like the summation of Virgo being highly critical and a neat freak. 

Sure, maybe those are aspects of the sign, but when I think of Virgo and the energy of this time of year, I think of the first harvest and mysteries the hermit has to teach us. 

I think about how good it feels to venture inward and recalibrate one’s mental processes after the social pomp and circumstance of Leo season. 

Virgo makes me ponder the multifaceted archetype of Mercury as a psychopomp, and Persephone’s journey to the underworld. 

Hot take — I don’t think Hades took Persephone against her will, I think she had full agency and chose to descend into the realm of the shadows to become acquainted with the dead, and fully know herself through meeting the demons living in her own heart. Level 10 shadow work.

“If there are demons to be met (in this coming dark season), surely they come from your own heart.” — @meaganangus 

Studying the wheel of the year with @meaganangus over the last 8(!!!) years has been an incredible tool in building my vocabulary around these magical archetypes and their corresponding seasons. She’s the real deal if you’re looking to dive deeper into astrology, tarot, or the esoteric mysteries in general.

I hit a pretty important milestone today and I wanted to share… Here’s a selfie of me from this week and a collection of highlights from the last few years to celebrate my 🎉fourth year anniversary🎉 of working at @lilithtattooseattle and my 🍾5 years🍾 of tattooing!!! 

I don’t really know how to put into words what it has meant to me to find a creative community like this one, especially after so many years of feeling like I didn’t belong anywhere. 

My art practice has absolutely taken off due to being surrounded by wildly talented, experienced, and skilled tattooers who have treated me as a peer and as a friend. 

Many of you who know me personally know that my apprenticeship was incredibly dysfunctional, but it got my foot in the door. Leaving that situation to come work at Lilith is one of the best and hardest decisions I’ve ever made. 

Waking up every day in an endlessly chaotic and violent world has been made exponentially easier having this place as my anchor. The connections I’ve been able to make with other artists and clients have been so special. I can’t adequately describe what the last few years have meant to me. I’ve grown so much as a person and as an artist.

Learning to tattoo has changed my life immeasurably. It is a skill that has such a steep, long, and slow learning curve. There is no hiding or “fake-it-til-you-make-it” with this craft, either you have put in the time or you haven’t, and it shows in every single line. It’s so challenging that it feels rewarding to see how far I’ve come. 

I’m grateful I didn’t give up every time it felt too hard. I’ve learned so much and I simultaneously feel like I’m just getting started. I now know I can do anything.

Thanks for sitting in my chair, for working alongside me, and for providing sweetness, inspiration, and connection in a word full of unfathomable horrors. All my love to the tattooers (past and present) and clients of @lilithtattooseattle , and especially to @judeletronik_tattoo. Jude is one of the kindest, most compassionate, generous, talented, and loving friends/mentors I’ve ever had. I wouldn’t be where I am without their support. 

Okay that’s it. You can go back to doomscrolling.

I love doing belly tattoos. Soft and abundant bellies are majestic canvases worthy of being adorned with ornate art. 

Getting to collaborate on decorating such a special and vulnerable part of the body feels magical and ritualistic to me on so many levels. 

Choosing to call attention to a sacred part of our bodies that we are traditionally taught to scorn, hide, or cover is a powerful act of self reclamation. It is a conscious choice to stand in your personal power, eschew shame, heal old wounds, and step into your confidence. 

Our sensuous, soft, luxurious bellies are the root of all of our joys, our mirth, our pleasures and delights.

Our bodies naturally ebb and flow like the moon. We are not meant to be stagnant and unchanging. We wax and wane with the seasons. To strive for a fixed, unchanged, and “ideal” image of ourselves is a symptom of living in a patriarchal, white supremacist, capitalist society. 

Imagine for a moment that you’re perfect exactly as you are. Maybe all the wisdom you need about your body already exists inside of it — it’s whispered to us when we pay attention to our natural cycles and our internal rhythms. 

Our seasonal iterations have so much more to teach us than “wellness” influencers or buzzy articles that claim to teach us about health. 

If you needed a reminder to take a deep breath today and spend some quality time adoring your belly, this is it.

When my books opened last May, new client Brianne emailed me a custom proposal that I was thrilled to take on! I finally got to do it this week.

Brianne requested that I make a piece inspired by the work of Jacques Fabien Gautier d’Agoty, a French anatomist, painter and printmaker from the 1700s. They asked for my iteration of this piece (but with wings!!!) for a tummy placement! I said hell yes. Tattooing scorpios is the best because y’all are down to go on the gnarliest philosophical deep dives with me, you want the wildest shit tattooed, and you love the pain 😅😂🖤

I *love* making menacing, creepy, gory, macabre, demonic, and otherwise nightmarish tattoos. I especially enjoy the intersection of elegance and terror, beauty and the grotesque, the sacred and the profane. To be alive is to contain these multitudes of light and shadow. To be human is to touch the immense and immeasurable horrors of existence and to also experience the gleaming sheen of the sublime. 

Swipe for the original piece that I used as a reference for my design. 

Thanks for looking!

FAB/RISING 
@fabtatt X @promethearising collab⚜️🌟💛🥇🏆👑

One of my favorite things about tattooing is that no matter how much I learn, I always feel brand new at it. I also love being a part of a community that is invested in sharing techniques, swapping best practices, and sending our rad clients to one another! Community > competition. We all have so much to learn from each other. 

My friend Franky has some impressive color skills (and intense color theory knowledge honed and developed from working a decade in the MUA industry). 

Recently, Franky reached out to me wanting to pick my brain about the admin side of tattooing, how I went from zero clients to filling my schedule for half a year at a time. Coincidentally, I have been admiring Franky’s work ever since I met them as an apprentice and got their first gold tattoo early on in their career that looks PERFECT to this day. 

So, we spent our day off together just gabbing and picking each other’s brains. It was SO fun and nourishing for me! Franky walked me through every step of his process for designing and creating a gold toned color tattoo. We took turns and did this piece in collaboration according to Franky’s method, while giving me a little license to play around! 

Hanging with this Capricorn angel as we’re in the thick of ♑️ szn was super inspiring to me, and I have a fire lit under my ass now for my future tattoo goals. It’s never a bad idea to pause and take time to hone your skills, redirect, and learn something new. The knowledge I got from Franky will inform every single piece I ever make from here on out. Thank you again for having me!

Many thanks to Mason @october__slime for being our handsome guinea pig and letting me practice on him 🏆😂 so glad I didn’t mess up. Haha. 

TL;DR — @fabtatt is really chill and talented and a great teacher, go follow & get tattooed by Franky !!!

I know I say this every time I post but I have hundreds of photos in my archive I need to share. There’s no rhyme or reason over here either. 

I don’t post on a schedule. I post when I feel like it. I have no interest in “growing my following” or whatever. In fact, I should post unhinged nonsense more often just to thin the herd a little bit! 🤣 

Most of my focus these days goes into researching for custom pieces, drawing, furthering my art education through independent study (100% self taught, baby!), learning new techniques and honing established ones in my tattoo practice, actually tattooing, and connecting with my clients. I’m grateful that social media has connected me with such amazing people but I’m also tired of it 😂. 

Anyway here’s some tats. I don’t know when my books will open again. I don’t have a waitlist. I’ve been booking my life out for 6 months at least since @lilithtattooseattle reopened in 2020 and I’m feeling it. 

I love this work more than anything, and I need to drastically cut back on my work load this year. I’ve been tattooing five days a week for many months now and I don’t really have a life outside of work anymore. This is why I’m planning to take some lengthy time off this summer to work on other creative projects and come back with a bang.
